FBIS4-876 "drafr077_e_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-077 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia New Justice Minister Urges Fighters To Turn in Arms New Justice Minister Urges Fighters To Turn in Arms AB2104103094 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 21 Apr 94 AB2104103094 Monrovia Radio ELBC English BFN [Text] Liberia's new justice minister, Councillor Laveli Supuwood, has called on fighters to turn in their arms and work toward enhancing the peace process. Minister Supuwood was speaking yesterday at the Executive Mansion following the commissioning of he and three other NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia] nominees confirmed yesterday by the Transitional Assembly. He said Liberians should not be deprived of their peace and freedom of movement only to satisfy a handful of people. Minister Supuwood also called on the international community, friendly governments, and the business community to recognize the Liberian National Transitional Government, saying it is the legitimate government of the people of Liberia.
